{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2011}} {{Use Australian English|date=August 2011}} {{Infobox Australian place | type = protected | name = Cape Nelson State Park | state = vic | iucn_category = III | image = Cape Nelson lighthouse VIC 1.jpg | caption = Cape Nelson lighthouse | image_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|38|25|18|S|141|32|28|E|display=inline,title}} | relief = yes | map_alt = | nearest_town_or_city = [[Portland, Victoria|Portland]] | area = 2.43 | area_footnotes = | established = | established_footnotes = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_footnotes = | managing_authorities = [[Parks Victoria]] | url = parkweb.vic.gov.au/explore/parks/cape-nelson-state-park }} The '''Cape Nelson State Park''', near [[Portland, Victoria|Portland]] on [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]]'s southwest coast is a {{convert|243|ha|adj=on}} state park.<ref name=PV>{{cite web|title=Cape Nelson State Park|url=http://parkweb.vic.gov.au/explore/parks/cape-nelson-state-park|work=Official website|publisher=[[Parks Victoria]]|accessdate=2012-01-27}}</ref> Attractions include a {{convert|3|km|0|adj=on}} clifftop walk and a visit to the Cape Nelson lighthouse. The lighthouse was completed in 1884 and today offers accommodation in the Light Station Keepers Cottages.<ref>[http://www.australiangeographic.com.au/travel/destinations/2010/07/australias-iconic-lighthouses/ Australia’s iconic lighthouses], Australian Geographic, 26 July 2010</ref> Part of the route of the [[Great South West Walk]] is located within the park.<ref name=chapman>{{cite web|url=http://www.john.chapman.name/vic-gsww.html|title=Great South West Walk|work=Victorian bushwalking|author=Chapman, John|location=Laburnum|publisher=John Chapman|date=9 October 2011|accessdate=21 August 2014}}</ref>
Fauna include the [[Heath Mouse]], [[Red-necked Wallaby]] and [[Echidna]]. The main vegetation types are listed as [[Soap Mallee]], [[Heath (habitat)|Heath]] and [[Wet Heath]].
The Cape Nelson lighthouse featured in the 2010 romantic drama ''[[South Solitary]]''.<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/search/title?locations=Cape%20Nelson,%20Victoria,%20Australia Film Titles With Location Matching "Cape Nelson, Victoria, Australia"]. International Movie Data Base (IMDb), retrieved 25 Feb 2012.</ref> The film provides good coverage of the interior of the lighthouse, cottage features and the landscape.
